The Libro.fm
Terms of Use
and this Privacy Policy describe the terms and conditions applicable to your access and use of the Service.
Please note that different privacy terms may apply to you based on where you live. Make sure you read the jurisdiction specific privacy terms for your country of residence located at the bottom of this Privacy Policy. There are currently jurisdiction specific privacy terms for users in Canada, the United Kingdom, Australia, and New Zealand as set out in Sections 12, 13, 14, and 15. Â The jurisdiction specific section might include additional information required under your local dataÂ â€protection laws, and may render certain aspects of the general Privacy Policy to be inapplicable, orÂ â€amend them accordingly to ensure compliance with your local data protection and privacy laws. As such, please beÂ â€sure you review this Privacy Policy in its entirety.â€
By using or interacting with the Service, you are entering into a binding contract with Libro.fm and acknowledge the use of your information as explained in this Privacy Policy. If you donâ€™t agree with these terms, then please donâ€™t use the Service.
2. Information we collect
This Privacy Policy relates to â€œpersonal dataâ€, â€œpersonal informationâ€ or â€œdataâ€, which are terms used by privacy â€and personal data regulators used around the world to cover the same type of data or â€information: that is, data or information that is information about you as an identifiable individual or that â€can be linked to you as an identifiable individual.
Information We Collect Directly From You.Â The type of information that we collect from you depends on your interaction with our Site and Services.
You must create an account to purchase audiobooks or memberships from the Site. To create an account, you must provide your name, email address, country, postal code or zip code, and password. You can also choose to support a specific bookstore. Â We also may collect additional optional information from you such as how you heard about us and other contact information.
If you become a member or make a purchase, you must provide your payment information, country, and zip code or postal code to our payment processor. For a purchase requiring shipment, we will collect your shipping address.
We will also collect information about your purchases, returns, gifts and recipients, statistics about your accomplishments as a listener and bookstore supporter, preferences such as language and genre and your email and club type when you sign up for book clubs.
If you refer a friend, we will collect the contact information you provide and may provide you with referral credits.
Through its Audiobook Listening Copy (â€œALCâ€) program, Libro.fm provides promotional copies of audiobooks to influencers, press, educators, librarians, and owners and employees of bookstore partners. If you apply for, or participate in, one of these ALC programs, we will collect your name and contact information and information to determine your qualification for the ALC program, including associated organizations, and social media channels for influencers. If you participate in one of the ALC programs, you agree that Libro.fm may share your name, organization, email address, social media and internet profiles, and ALC download activity with publishers and others as part of our ALC Program. The publisherâ€™s use of your personal information is governed by their privacy policy.
Libro.fm provides audiobooks to corporations and other organizations for distribution to employees and other recipients chosen by the organization. If you receive an audiobook from an organization, we may provide your name, email address and which book(s) you received to the organization in accordance with our agreement with the organization. The organizationâ€™s use of your personal information is governed by their privacy policy.
Information We Collect Automatically.Â We automatically collect the following information about your use of our Site or Services and your device through cookies, web beacons, and other technologies: your domain name; your browser type and operating system; device information; web pages you view on our Site; links you click on our Site; your IP address; the length of time you visit our Site and or use our Services; and the referring URL or the webpage that led you to our Site. We will collect information about your purchases, quizzes, recommendations, preferences, playlists, and other activities on the Site and Services.
Cookies and Other Technologies
Like many websites, we employ "cookies" on the Site and Service to allow us to provide and improve your experience. Cookies are small bits of electronic information that a website sends to a visitor's browser. Each user is assigned a â€œcookie IDâ€ from our Site domain in connection with the registration process. We use cookies, including your cookie ID, to store a user's log-in identity when you re-access the Site; to monitor irregular account behavior and to prevent fraud; and to generate and compile aggregated statistics that allow us to understand how users navigate our Site and Service. You may refuse the use of certain cookies by selecting the appropriate settings on your browser or device; however, if you do this, you may not be able to use the full functionality of the Site and Service.
Log Information
We also keep track of your interaction with the Site, Service and any other users. Specifically, our servers automatically record information that your browser (or our Service) sends whenever you interact with the Service. This information includes your Internet Protocol address (IP address), your cookie ID, your browser type and version, mobile operating system, mobile device type, app version, which aspects of Service you use and when and how long you use them, and how you otherwise access the Libro.fm Service.
Do-Not-Track
Currently, our Site and Services do not recognize browser â€œdo-not-trackâ€ requests. You may, however, disable certain tracking as discussed in this section (e.g., by disabling cookies).
Third-Party Analytics
Our Site and Services may use services operated by third parties, such as Google Analytics, which uses cookies and similar technologies to collect and analyze information about use of the Sites and report on activities and trends. This service may also collect information regarding the use of other websites, apps and online resources. You can learn about Googleâ€™s practices by going to www.google.com/policies/privacy/partners/, and you can opt out of them by downloading the Google Analytics opt out browser add-on, available at Â https://tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout.
Social Plugins
We use Instagram, Facebook, X (formerly Twitter), TikTok, YouTube, and Vimeo social plugins on our Site. When you view a web page that contains a plugin, your browser will create a direct link to the third partiesâ€™ servers. If you are logged into your social media account, the social media platform will record the visit to your social media account. Please visit the social media platformâ€™s privacy policy for more information.
Third-Party Ad Networks
We use third parties such as network advertisers to serve advertisements on third-party websites or other media (e.g., social networking platforms). This enables us and these third parties to target advertisements to you for products and services in which you might be interested. Third-party ad network providers, advertisers, sponsors and/or traffic measurement services may use cookies, JavaScript, web beacons (including clear GIFs), Flash LSOs and other tracking technologies to measure the effectiveness of their ads and to personalize advertising content to you. These third-party cookies and other technologies are governed by each third partyâ€™s specific privacy policy, not this one. We may provide these third-party advertisers with information, including personal information, about you.
Users in the United States may opt out of many third-party ad networks. For example, you may go to the Digital Advertising Alliance (DAA)
Consumer Choice Page
for information about opting out of interest-based advertising and your choices.
Opting out from one or more companies listed on the DAA
Consumer Choice Page
will opt you out from those companiesâ€™ delivery of interest-based content or ads to you, but it does not mean you will no longer receive any advertising through our Site or on other websites. You may continue to receive advertisements, for example, based on the particular website that you are viewing (i.e., contextually based ads). Also, if your browsers are configured to reject cookies when you opt out on the DAA site, your opt out may not be effective. Additional information is available on the DAAâ€™s website at www.aboutads.info.
3. How we use your information
We may use the information we collect, including your personal information, to:
provide, personalize, and improve your experience with the Site, Services and Products, for example by providing customized or localized content such as bookstore finder, recommended books, event notices, or advertising;
ensure technical functioning of the Site and Service;
provide customer support, including facilitating returns and refunds;
develop new products, services and recommendations, and analyze your use of the Site, Services, and Products including your interaction with applications, advertising, Products and Services;
communicate with you, including promotional emails or messages;
enable and promote the Site and Services, including features, playlists, wish lists and content, such as sharing, user interactions, notifications and suggestions, and integration with third party services;
allow you to participate in events, contests, sweepstakes, promotions, giveaways, look up bookstores and other similar activities;
enforce this Privacy Policy and the Libro.fm Terms of Use, including to protect the rights, property or safety of us, users or any other person and the copyright-protected content; and
as otherwise stated in this Privacy Policy or through our notice to you.
